        <div class="content-body">
            <form class="ml-4 mr-4 " style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51);" action="/<%= websiteName %>/setting" method="post">
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <label for="exampleInputEmail1" class="form-label text-primary">
                        <h3>Domain</h3>
                    </label>
                    <p class="text-warning">Before changing the domain of your website, please note that this action
                        will update the URL associated with your site. Ensure all your links and external references are
                        updated accordingly to avoid any broken links or access issues. Changing the domain is a
                        significant action that affects how users access your website via its new URL.</p>
                    <input type="text" value="<%= websiteName %>" class="form-control" name="domain"
                        style="max-width: 300px;">
                </div>
                <hr class="border  border-3 opacity-75">

                <div class="mb-3">
                    <label for="exampleInputPassword1" class="form-label text-primary">
                        <h3>Default page</h3>
                    </label>
                    <p class="text-warning">When changing the default main page of your website, ensure that the new
                        page accurately represents your site's content and purpose. Update any internal links within
                        your website to direct visitors to the new main page. This change can influence how users
                        interact with your site and find relevant information upon their visit.</p>
                    <input type="text" value="<%= defaultPageName %>" class="form-control" name="defaultPageName"
                        style="max-width: 300px;">
                </div>
                <hr class="border  border-3 opacity-75">
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <label for="exampleInputPassword1" class="form-label text-primary">
                        <h3>Website Visibility</h3>
                    </label>
                    <p class="text-warning">When you make your website public, it becomes accessible to anyone on the
                        internet. This setting is suitable for websites intended for general visibility and
                        accessibility.<br>Conversely, making your website private restricts access to only authorized
                        users or those with specific credentials. This setting is useful for websites that contain
                        confidential information or are intended for a limited audience.<br>Ensure to choose the
                        appropriate setting based on your website's purpose and the level of access you want to grant to
                        visitors.</p>
                    <div class="form-check">
                        <input class="form-check-input" name="visibility" type="radio" value="true" <% if (visibility) {
                            %> checked <% } %>>
                            <label class="form-check-label" for="flexCheckDefault">
                                Public
                            </label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-check">
                        <input class="form-check-input" name="visibility" type="radio" value="false" <% if (!visibility)
                            { %> checked <% } %>>
                            <label class="form-check-label text-danger bold" for="flexCheckChecked">
                                Private
                            </label>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary pl-4 pr-4 mb-3">Make Changes</button>
                <hr class="border  border-1 opacity-100">
                <p class="text-warning">This action will <span class="text-danger">permanently delete</span> this site,
                    you cant recover this site</p>
                <script>
                    function showModel() {
                        console.log("Hello")
                        document.getElementById('filter').style.display = 'block'
                    }
                </script>
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-danger" onclick="showModel()">delete website</button>
            </form>

